Whe JSON Web Token

- JWT a good choice to be passed into HTML and HTTP env due to it smaller footprint
- can be signed using shared secret and public key.
- easier to work with JWT as JSON as common in most programming.
- suitable for implementing authorization in large-scale web app.

JWT Structure

- Header:

  - type of token, e.g: JWT
  - signing algo: SHA512

- Payload:
  - provide info about user & other info like token expiry time.

Uses cases:

- Authorization:
  - user login & each subsequent request will include the JWT allowing the user to access routes, sevice and resources that are permitted with that token.
